column5: Not sure if this has been posted on here yet, but it's a really nice site with an interactive map showing angling opportunities in Ontario.  Great for those looking for a new lake to try out.  http://www.web2.mnr.gov.on.ca/fish_online/fishing/fishingExplorer_en.html  Cheers.
Yes it was posted by Ron about 10 days ago but thanks for the reminder.  http://www.ofncommunity.com/forums/index.php?showtopic=52646
Hey thanks alot for posting that I wasn't able to be on the computer for the past few weeks to often so I appreciate you posting it again I find it very interesting and can come in helpful.
That is very well made!  Allthough it shows a couple lakes that I though I was the only one who knew about them...lol  Not sure how acurate the fish listings are though...
Well there goes my honey hole. lol
from what i've seen of it so far... not very...  pretty cool idea... but doesn't seem to be as accurate as it should be.
Strange how they don't even know the name of Canal Lake, it's just 'unnamed water body'.
